                type="chemical">
               <term xml:id="tag133">
          Chlorite
          
        </term>
            </rs>.- <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">Instance</hi>.-<lb/>
- But when a bright green<lb/>
powder, or crystallized substance<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="16"
                xml:id="pb-16"
                facs="#i16"/>
            <lb/>
is found it indicates <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag134"
                ref="#chemical_070"
                type="chemical">
               <term xml:id="tag134">
                  <hi rend="underline">copper</hi>
               </term>
            </rs> |_ And<lb/>
the tint itself, is almost always<lb/>
owing to the presence of <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag135"
